President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Massachusetts due to the effects of Hurricane Irene. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to identify and provide necessary equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. The federal funding for emergency protective measures, including direct assistance, will be provided at a rate of 75 percent. James N. Russo has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.